# Data Model (Prisma, MySQL)

Primary schema: app/prisma/schema.prisma. The microservice has a subset schema under microservice/prisma/schema.prisma aligned with main models used for rotation/migration.

Note: Several string fields are annotated with prisma-field-encryption (/// @encrypted). The generator fieldEncryptionMigrations produces app/prisma/reencrypt/*.

## Core entities

- Account
  - Root container for a user's financial workspace; has many Budgets, AccountRegisters, Categories, Reoccurrences, Snapshots
- User
  - Encrypted email, optional password (hashed), role (USER/ADMIN), timezone/country
  - Relations: UserAccount (membership), PlaidItem, Notifications, Dismissals
- UserAccount
  - Membership in Accounts with permission flags and allowlists (allowedBudgetIds, allowedAccountRegisterIds)
- AccountInvite + AccountInviteAccount
  - Multi-account invites with permission flags and allowlists

## Budgeting and registers

- Budget
  - Per-account budget; has AccountRegisters and links to BillProfile/Instance, savings goals, notifications, reconciliation periods
- AccountRegister
  - Represents a ledger/account within a budget: checking, credit card, loan, asset, crypto wallet, etc.
  - Many finance‑specific fields (APR tiers, loan details, collateral links, min balances, statement interval)
  - Encrypted: name, plaid secrets/wallet address where applicable
  - Relations:
    - type: AccountType (registerClass, isCredit, accruesBalanceGrowth)
    - entries: RegisterEntry[]
    - reoccurrences: Reoccurrence[]
    - collateralAsset / loansSecuredByAsset (self relations)
    - paymentCategory / interestCategory defaults (Category)
    - snapshots, savings goal links, cashOnHand (1:1), cryptoRegisterChains, cryptoTokenBalances
- RegisterEntry
  - Transactions in a register (amount, balance, timestamps, flags for projected/pending/reconciled, etc.)
  - Encrypted: description, plaidId
  - Optional type via RegisterEntryType (name)

## Categories

- Category
  - Hierarchical (parent/children via subCategoryId), per-account; functional unique constraint in migrations prevents duplicates by name within (account, parent)
  - Used by RegisterEntry, Reoccurrence, ReoccurrenceSplit, AccountRegister payment/interest defaults, SavingsGoal

## Reoccurrences and splits

- Reoccurrence
  - Scheduled repeating item (amount, description encrypted, interval and count, optional transfer target)
  - Optional amount adjustment rules (mode, direction, value, interval, anchor)
  - Relations: entries, skips, splits, plaid name aliases, BillProfile/Instances
- ReoccurrenceSplit
  - Split of a reoccurrence into transfer lines with amount mode (FIXED/PERCENT), category, and order; targets another AccountRegister
- ReoccurrenceSkip
  - Skipped occurrences for a given account/register
- ReoccurrencePlaidNameAlias
  - Normalized names used to match Plaid transactions to reoccurrences per register

## Bills and reconciliation

- BillProfile (BILL/INCOME/TRANSFER)
  - 1:1 with a Reoccurrence; stores payee, autopay, expected amount bounds, priority, reminders
- BillInstance
  - Instantiated bills at due dates with status, payment linkage to a RegisterEntry
- ReconciliationPeriod (+ ReconciliationItem)
  - Statement window, opening/ending balances, status (OPEN/CLOSED), difference and closing adjustments

## Savings and summaries

- SavingsGoal
  - Source and target registers, amount target, sorting, priority flags, optional category
- AccountSnapshot + AccountRegisterSnapshot + RegisterEntrySnapshot
  - Snapshot hierarchy capturing point‑in‑time balances and entries
- AccountRegisterSummary
  - Rolling monthly/yearly summaries per register

## Integrations and logs

- PlaidItem, PlaidSyncCursor, PlaidSyncLog
  - Link users to Plaid items, track cursor, and detailed sync logs (mode, status, tx counts, durations, errors)
- IntegrationAlert, IntegrationJobLog
  - Generic alerting/logging artifacts for integrations and background jobs
- OpenAiRequestLog
  - Tracks OpenAI requests for auditing/metrics

## Crypto and assets

- EvmChain
  - Chain catalog (network id, symbol, explorer)
- CryptoRegisterChain
  - Which chains a crypto register targets
- CryptoTokenBalance
  - Synced token balances and market values per register/network/token
- Asset fields on AccountRegister for depreciation and vehicle details

## Intervals and types

- Interval
  - Named schedule intervals (shared by reoccurrence and account statement intervals)
- AccountType
  - Logical register type plus flags (class, isCredit, accruesBalanceGrowth)
- RegisterEntryType
  - Named classifications for entries; used by ledger logic

## Encryption support

- Encrypted fields include:
  - User.email, User.password (hashed), AccountRegister.name, plaid secret fields, walletAddress; RegisterEntry.description, plaidId; Reoccurrence.description
- Generators:
  - generator fieldEncryptionMigrations produces reencrypt/ modules for automated migrate/re-encrypt flows
- Re-encryption paths:
  - app/prisma/reencrypt/* and microservice/prisma/reencrypt/* provide generated migrators
  - docs/post-restore-encryption-plan.md documents local restore behavior and placeholders

